    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Circular saws that are set below the surface of a table having a slot through which the saw blade protrudes.(DAC) The blade can be raised or lowered to control the depth of cut, and it can usually be tilted to provide a cut of a particular angle. The same equipment may be described as "bench saws."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000010771/Harris, Dictionary of Architecture and Construction (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cirkelzagen die onder het blad van een tafel zijn gemonteerd waarin een gleuf zit waardoor ze  omhoog steken. Het zaagblad kan omhoog of omlaag worden gebracht om de diepte van de zaagsnede te bepalen en kan meestal worden gekanteld om onder een bepaalde hoek te kunnen zagen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kreissäge, die unterhalb der Oberfläche eines Tisches mit einem Schlitz sitzt, durch den das Sägeblatt herausragt. Das Blatt kann angehoben oder abgesenkt werden, um die Schnitttiefe zu regulieren, und es kann gewöhnlich geneigt werden, um einen Schnitt aus einem bestimmten Winkel zu bieten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
